  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Credit Risk Manager – Commodity Trading Firm",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking an experienced and highly analytical <strong>Credit Risk Manager</strong> to join our dynamic team at a leading <strong>commodity trading firm</strong>. This role is critical in overseeing the credit risk function across a diverse portfolio of counterparties, including producers, traders, industrials, and financial institutions, in both developed and emerging markets.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct in-depth credit analysis of counterparties including financial institutions, corporates, and state-owned entities.</li><li>Assign internal credit ratings and recommend risk-based exposure limits.</li><li>Perform ongoing monitoring and early warning analysis of credit risk profiles.</li><li>Oversee and monitor the firm's credit exposure across physical and derivative commodity transactions.</li><li>Work closely with front office, legal, and operations teams to manage structured trades and mitigate risk.</li><li>Ensure compliance with risk appetite, internal policies, and regulatory requirements.</li></ul><p><strong> Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelors’ degree in a related field</li><li>At least 8 years of Credit Risk experience</li><li>Prior Compliance experience in a Trading house, ideally in Agri</li><li>Able to work independently</li><li>Ability to manage and work with regional stakeholders</li></ul><p>Take charge of this opportunity to welcome a new career challenge in 2025</p><p> <br />EA Personnel No R1985201<br />BeathChapman Pte Ltd<br />Licence No 16S8112</p>",
